{
  "texts": [
    "The logical subspace is obtained by projecting ρ phys onto the logical subspace 33,34.",
    "We obtain the elements of the density matrix of the logical subspace ρ using the equationρ k l ρ m n P =, (2)kl mn L, phys | |where k, l, m, n = 0, 1 specify orthogonal vectors in the logical subspace and| | P kl ρ k l = ∑ L kl,is the probability that the state we prepare is in the logical subspace.",
    "Using this method, we obtain the projected logical infidelity for the error-suppressed procedure as (1.70 ± 0.35) × 10 -2 with the probability of finding ρ phys in the logical subspace P L = 0.898 ± 0.008.",
    "An average post-selection acceptance rate over all physical Pauli directions is found to be 14.9 ± 0.1%.",
    "This projected logical infidelity is shown as the rightmost blue data point in Fig. 3 to be compared with the central blue data point."
  ]
}